Module chav1961.purelib

Package chav1961.purelib.basic

This package contains a set of classes for the basic abilities of the library. They includes:

  • a set of logger facades (implements LoggerFacade interface) to prevent your application from the ZOO of huge amount of loggers and reduce logger trace due to different criteria
  • AbstractScriptEngine and it's children to support scripting languages in your library
  • AndOrTree and OrdinalSyntaxTree classes to implement quick name/id tree for using in the parsers
  • ArgParser class to parse and manage of command line arguments for your application
  • BitCharSet and ExtendedBitCharSet classes to quick classification of the characters (similar to Character.isDigit(char) or Character.isJavaIdentifierPart(char) methods)
  • CharUtils class, containing a set of static methods to parse, print and manipulate of character arrays and strings. It's strongly recommended to use them in your compilers
  • ConsoleCommandManager class to implement simple-and-easy console command processing in the Java console-oriented applications
  • FSM and StackedFSM classed to support finite state machines in your applications
  • GettersAndSettersFactory class to build raw assemble code for fast access to instance fields of any classes
  • LineByLineProcessor class for quick splitting input source to lines and support it's line-by-line processing
  • LongIdMap class to implement quick tree with long ID as key
  • PluggableClassLoader class to implement simple plug-in mechanism in your application
  • PureLibSettings class as a center of all the Pure Library settings
  • ReusableInstances class to support cache of reusable class instances for reducing memory allocations in your application
  • SequenceIterator class for simple joining a set of iterators to one total iterator
  • SimpleURLClassLoader class for defining new classes (both with raw class file data and source assembly code - see AsmWriter)
  • SubstitutableProperties class to process property files content with automatic substitutions and data conversions
  • TemporaryStore class to use temporary memory-to-disk-growable files
  • URIUtils class, containing a set of static methods to manage URIs.
  • Utils class, containing a set of useful methods to use in your applicaiton.
  • XMLUtils class, containing a set of static methods to manage XML.
